Hey! Welcome to the website of University of South Carolina,  Columbia. I can help you with some basic questions regarding application,  locations,  student housing,  dining on campus,  etc. How can I help you?
Hey boy, How to find a place to stay?
The campus housing is mainly for freshmen students. Most of univeristy's students and visitors use off-campus housing. Many find www.zillow.com useful for finding an appartment or a room.
Hey boy, How much is the application fee?
The application fee for undergradute is $65 (Common Application Fee without waiver);for general graduate program is $50. Other applications may cost more.
Hey boy, How's about the student housing

The resident on-campus housing price varies from $3100 to $6600 per semester. For more details,  please refer to the webpage: https://sc.edu/about/offices_and_divisions/housing/index.php; The off-campus apartment price in Columbia ranges from 500-1500 USD. A room can be found at 350-600 USD. Columbia offers a range of traditional,  family-friendly housing options and apartments. You can widen your search on websites such as ApartmentFinder.com,  ApartmentList.com,  Zillow.com,  Trulia.com,  and Homes.com.
Hey boy, Where to have lunch on campus?
There's a number of lunch places within and around the campus. Please see the lunch places here https://sc.edu/experience/grab_a_bite/campus_restaurants_list.php
